2
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:37,000
あ、あ、あ、
Ah, ah, ah...

3
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,500
皆様、おーー！
Everyone, wooah!

4
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:43,000
いいね、コメント元気だね。
Great, you are so energetic in the comments!

5
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:47,800
本日は風真いろは生誕ライブ2026、
Today is Kazama Iroha's Birthday Live 2026,

6
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:51,200
「Wind Trails」にご来場くださいまして、
thank you so much for coming to "Wind Trails"!

7
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,800
誠にありがとうございます！いぇーい！
Thank you very much! Yay!

8
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:59,000
開演に先立ちまして、皆様にお願いとご案内を申し上げます。
Prior to the show starting, I have some requests and info for you.

9
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:04,500
開演中、カメラやスマートフォンなどは、えー、電源切られると見れなくなって困るので、
During the show, if you turn off your cameras or smartphones, you won't be able to watch,

10
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:08,500
電源は切らず、写真撮影などね、大量にしていただき、
so keep them on, take tons of screenshots,

11
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:14,200
当配信のハッシュタグ、#風真いろは生誕ライブ2026 で
and please use our official hashtag, #風真いろは生誕ライブ2026...

12
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:17,800
SNSに大量に画像ポストしてください！
...to post tons of photos on social media!

13
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:23,500
目指せ、Xトレンド1位！よろしくお願いいたします！
Let's aim for #1 on X trends! Please help make it happen!

14
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:29,800
あ、あの、でもスマホね、いっぱい写真撮ったりすると充電なくなっちゃいそうなんで、
Ah, but taking so many photos might drain your battery,

15
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:33,200
スマホで見てる勢は、えー、充電しっかりしてくださいね。
so those watching on smartphones, make sure your phone is charged!

16
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:35,000
はい、そして、その2！
Alright, and number two!

17
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,500
激しく頭を振る、えー、激しくペンライトを振る、などはですね、
Violent headbanging or waving your penlight too hard...

18
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:44,800
あなた様のご自宅を破壊する危険性がございますので、
...poses a danger of destroying your home.

19
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:50,000
あの、破壊されてもですね、こちらは責任一切負えませんので、
Even if it gets destroyed, we cannot take any responsibility...

20
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,000
あの、お気をつけください。ダメだよ、みんな。
...so please be careful! Don't do it, guys!

21
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,200
あ、そしてあと、もういっこ。その3。
Oh, and one more thing! Number three.

22
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:59,800
あの、今からハヤシライスを準備しようとしてる奴は間に合わないからやめな。
If you're trying to make hayashi rice right now, you won't make it in time, so stop.

23
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:02,000
絶対間に合わないから。
You definitely won't make it in time.

24
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:07,500
まあね、何か食べたり飲んだりしながら、ぜひね、ゆっくり楽しんでもらえると嬉しいです！
Anyway, I hope you enjoy the show at your own pace while eating or drinking something!

25
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,500
それでは、もうそろそろ始まるので、
Well then, the show is starting soon,

26
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,000
今しばらくお待ちください。
so please wait just a little longer.

27
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
最後まで見てねーー！
Make sure to watch until the very end!

28
00:05:02,048 --> 00:05:08,548
風真いろは生誕ライブ 2026 行くよー！
Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026! Here we go!

29
00:05:11,848 --> 00:05:13,548
いっせーのーで
Ready, set, go!

30
00:05:13,548 --> 00:05:16,848
鳴り響いたスタートの合図
The start signal rang out

31
00:05:17,048 --> 00:05:20,348
なぞった線で 結んだ世界
A world connected by lines that I traced

32
00:05:20,348 --> 00:05:22,548
色付けていく
I'll start adding color

33
00:05:22,548 --> 00:05:25,048
ここから
From here

34
00:05:33,248 --> 00:05:37,848
物心つく頃 すでに此処にあった
It was already here when I became aware

35
00:05:38,248 --> 00:05:41,048
僕じゃない誰かの記憶は
Memories that aren't mine...

36
00:05:41,048 --> 00:05:44,048
夕陽とともに蘇る
...awaken with the setting sun

37
00:05:44,248 --> 00:05:48,548
古ぼけた絵本を取り出して
I took out the worn-out picture book

38
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:54,048
落書きの中に1つの答えを見つけた
And found one answer in the scribbles

39
00:05:54,248 --> 00:05:57,248
自分の価値に 目を疑って
Doubting my own worth with my eyes

40
00:05:57,248 --> 00:06:00,048
どこまでだって 堕ちていけるの
How far can I fall?

41
00:06:00,048 --> 00:06:02,548
どこか遠くに 消えてしまいたい
I want to disappear somewhere far away

42
00:06:02,548 --> 00:06:05,448
こんな世界じゃ僕はいらない
I don't need myself in a world like this

43
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,548
カウントダウンは
The countdown...

44
00:06:07,548 --> 00:06:10,048
始まっているよ
...has already begun

45
00:06:11,048 --> 00:06:13,348
“いっせーのー”で 声を上げて
Raise your voice at the signal of "Ready-go"

46
00:06:13,348 --> 00:06:15,848
聴こえてくるんだ
I can hear it

47
00:06:15,848 --> 00:06:19,048
自分の影の 長さに気づく
I notice the length of my own shadow

48
00:06:19,048 --> 00:06:21,048
もうこんな時間だ
It's already this late

49
00:06:21,048 --> 00:06:24,048
一等星が 顔を出した
A first-magnitude star showed its face

50
00:06:24,048 --> 00:06:26,548
届きそうで 手を伸ばした
I stretched out my hand as if I could reach it

51
00:06:26,548 --> 00:06:29,548
“次は僕についてきな”と
"Follow me next time," it said

52
00:06:29,548 --> 00:06:32,048
どんな暗闇でも
No matter how dark it is

53
00:06:32,048 --> 00:06:34,548
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet

54
00:06:34,548 --> 00:06:37,048
幕は上がりだした
The curtain began to rise

55
00:06:37,048 --> 00:06:39,548
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet

56
00:06:39,548 --> 00:06:44,048
色付けていく ここから
I'll start adding color here

57
00:06:53,048 --> 00:06:58,248
10年後の僕らは すれ違いばかりで
Ten years later, we are always passing each other by

58
00:06:58,248 --> 00:07:01,048
幻想に想いを馳せては
I let my thoughts race in illusions

59
00:07:01,048 --> 00:07:04,048
“戻れない”そう思い込んだ
Thinking, "I can't go back"

60
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:08,548
くたびれた心に 追い討ちを
Adding to my exhausted heart

61
00:07:08,548 --> 00:07:11,548
あの頃と変わらない夕陽も
Even the setting sun, which hasn't changed since those days...

62
00:07:11,548 --> 00:07:14,048
なんとも思わない
...I don't feel anything

63
00:07:14,248 --> 00:07:17,248
自分を信じ 歩いていければ
If I could just believe in myself and keep walking

64
00:07:17,248 --> 00:07:19,248
どこまでだって 昇れるのに
I could climb anywhere

65
00:07:20,048 --> 00:07:22,548
カットを跨ぐ その空白に
In the blank space that spans the shots

66
00:07:22,548 --> 00:07:24,548
大切なモノ 見落としている
I'm overlooking something important

67
00:07:25,048 --> 00:07:30,048
見つけられないと 泣きわめく君へ
To you who cries and screams that you can't find it

68
00:07:30,848 --> 00:07:33,348
“いっせーのー”で 声を上げて
Raise your voice at the signal of "Ready-go"

69
00:07:33,348 --> 00:07:35,848
聴こえてくるんだ
I can hear it

70
00:07:35,848 --> 00:07:38,848
自分の影の 長さに気づく
I notice the length of my own shadow

71
00:07:38,848 --> 00:07:40,848
もうこんな時間だ
It's already this late

72
00:07:40,848 --> 00:07:43,848
一等賞で 駆け抜ける君
You who run through as the first prize winner

73
00:07:43,848 --> 00:07:46,348
くっついていただけの僕でも
Even I, who only stuck with you

74
00:07:46,348 --> 00:07:49,048
君の前を 歩けるかな？
Can I walk in front of you?

75
00:07:49,048 --> 00:07:53,048
こんな頼りない 僕でも
Even I, who am so unreliable

76
00:08:13,048 --> 00:08:17,548
宝箱はホコリを かぶったまま
The treasure chest was covered in dust

77
00:08:17,548 --> 00:08:20,548
なくした鍵は ずっと
The lost key was always...

78
00:08:20,548 --> 00:08:23,048
君のポケットの中にあった
...in your pocket

79
00:08:23,048 --> 00:08:25,548
散らばっていた全てが
Everything that was scattered

80
00:08:25,548 --> 00:08:28,048
今ひとつに重なる
Is now overlapping into one

81
00:08:28,048 --> 00:08:31,048
手を取り始めよう
Let's start taking hands

82
00:08:31,048 --> 00:08:33,548
僕たちの物語
Our story

83
00:08:33,548 --> 00:08:39,048
一度は いらないと思った
I thought I didn't need it once

84
00:08:39,048 --> 00:08:46,048
今なら胸を張れる気がしたんだ
Now I feel like I can hold my head high

85
00:08:47,048 --> 00:08:52,048
愛おしくて
It's so dear

86
00:08:53,048 --> 00:08:55,848
掛け声はいつも
The shout of encouragement is always...

87
00:08:56,048 --> 00:09:00,048
“いっせーのー”で 声を上げて
Raise your voice at the signal of "Ready-go"

88
00:09:00,048 --> 00:09:03,048
聴こえてくるんだ
I can hear it

89
00:09:03,048 --> 00:09:05,548
自分の影の 長さに気づく
I notice the length of my own shadow

90
00:09:05,548 --> 00:09:07,548
もうこんな時間だ
It's already this late

91
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:11,048
一等星が 顔を出した
A first-magnitude star showed its face

92
00:09:11,048 --> 00:09:14,048
届きそうで 手を伸ばした
I stretched out my hand as if I could reach it

93
00:09:14,048 --> 00:09:17,048
“次は僕についてきな”と
"Follow me next time," it said

94
00:09:17,048 --> 00:09:19,548
どんな暗闇でも
No matter how dark it is

95
00:09:20,048 --> 00:09:22,548
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet

96
00:09:22,548 --> 00:09:25,048
泣きじゃくった声で
With a tearful voice

97
00:09:25,048 --> 00:09:27,548
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet

98
00:09:27,548 --> 00:09:30,548
笑う君が見えた
I saw you laughing

99
00:09:30,548 --> 00:09:33,048
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet

100
00:09:33,048 --> 00:09:36,548
幕は上がりだした
The curtain began to rise

101
00:09:36,548 --> 00:09:39,048
もういいかい？ もういいよ
Are you ready? Yes, it's okay

102
00:09:39,048 --> 00:09:44,048
色付けていく ここから
I'll start adding color here

103
00:10:15,123 --> 00:10:17,023
はい！ということで
Alright! And with that,

104
00:10:17,023 --> 00:10:19,823
始まりましたー！
it has begun!

105
00:10:20,123 --> 00:10:25,023
風真いろは生誕ライブ2026...
Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026...

106
00:10:25,023 --> 00:10:28,923
スタート！みんな、こんばんはー！
Start! Good evening, everyone!

107
00:10:29,023 --> 00:10:32,423
見えてるー？
Can you see me?

108
00:10:33,423 --> 00:10:36,523
はい、ということで、本日のハッシュタグはこちら！
Alright, so here is today's hashtag!

109
00:10:36,523 --> 00:10:38,223
こちらね、みんな、
Please use this one, everyone,

110
00:10:38,223 --> 00:10:43,023
いっぱいポストして、いっぱいカッコいいとこ撮ってくださいね、頼むよ！
post a lot and take lots of cool screenshots! I'm counting on you!

111
00:10:43,123 --> 00:10:46,023
この風真いろはがイケメンであることを
To let the world know

112
00:10:46,023 --> 00:10:48,523
世の中に知らしめられるのは、
that Kazama Iroha is cool...

113
00:10:48,523 --> 00:10:51,523
お前たち、お前たちだけなので、よろしくお願いします！
...is up to you guys! Only you can do it, so please help me out!

114
00:10:51,523 --> 00:10:55,023
はい、そして今回のねライブ、タイトルがついております！
Yes, and this live concert has a title!

115
00:10:55,123 --> 00:10:58,523
Wind Trails というね、
It's titled 'Wind Trails',

116
00:10:58,523 --> 00:11:00,823
タイトルがついておりますが、
and as for this title,

117
00:11:01,023 --> 00:11:04,123
ま、そのまんま訳して、結構お気づきの方も多かったんですが、
which, as many of you might have noticed from the literal translation,

118
00:11:04,223 --> 00:11:07,523
風の軌跡というね、あの、意味を込めて付けさせていただき、
carries the meaning of 'Trails of the Wind'.

119
00:11:07,523 --> 00:11:13,123
今回ライブ色々、頑張って考えさせていただきました！
I worked hard to plan various things for this live!

120
00:11:13,123 --> 00:11:16,223
なのでね、最後まで楽しんでもらえると嬉しいです！
So, I hope you enjoy it until the very end!

121
00:11:16,223 --> 00:11:21,023
そして、1曲目、かくれんぼ、歌わせていただきましたー！
And for the first song, I performed 'Kakurenbo'!

122
00:11:21,023 --> 00:11:23,523
どうだったかなー？
How did you like it?

123
00:11:24,023 --> 00:11:28,623
はい、そして今日、室内ライブだと思ったでしょ？
Also, you probably thought today was an indoor live, right?

124
00:11:28,723 --> 00:11:31,523
見てー！
Look!

125
00:11:31,523 --> 00:11:36,523
曲中に、ドームが開きましたー！イェーイ！
During the song, the dome opened up! Yay!

126
00:11:36,623 --> 00:11:38,923
すごーい！
Amazing!

127
00:11:39,023 --> 00:11:42,523
やっぱね、なかなか現地ライブって、できてもさ、
After all, even when we do live concerts in person,

128
00:11:42,523 --> 00:11:45,523
青空の下でなかなか歌うことってないので、
we rarely get to sing under the blue sky.

129
00:11:46,023 --> 00:11:49,023
いつか、俺たちとお前たちの次元が交ざって、
Maybe one day, our dimensions will merge

130
00:11:49,023 --> 00:11:53,023
空の下で歌えるような世界が来るかもしれないけど、
and we'll be able to sing under the real sky,

131
00:11:53,123 --> 00:11:57,123
やってみたくてね、今回は、空の下で歌うっていうこの演出やらせていただきましたー！
but I really wanted to try it, so I went with this outdoor performance stage today!

132
00:11:59,823 --> 00:12:02,023
めっちゃいいでしょ？
Isn't it great?

133
00:12:02,123 --> 00:12:04,123
で、ステージもめっちゃかっこいいんで、
And the stage is super cool too!

134
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:08,523
今日ね、多分いっぱい見る機会あると思いますが、
You'll probably see it a lot today,

135
00:12:08,523 --> 00:12:11,823
ゆっくり隅から隅まで
but feel free to check out every single corner,

136
00:12:11,823 --> 00:12:13,523
アーカイブ勢もね、きっといると思うんで、
including those watching the archive later.

137
00:12:13,623 --> 00:12:17,323
本当に色んな細部こだわってるんで、細かく見てくださいね！
We paid close attention to every detail, so please look closely!

138
00:12:17,523 --> 00:12:19,523
ということで、あ、お水飲んでいいですかね？
With that said, oh, can I drink some water?

139
00:12:22,023 --> 00:12:28,023
お水を、う、う、やめろ！俺の頭を、う、やめ、う、
Let me get some wa— Ah! Stop! My head— Hey, stop!

140
00:12:29,823 --> 00:12:32,423
頭をいじくり回されて、ヘッドセットになりました。
They messed with my head, and now I have a headset on.

141
00:12:32,423 --> 00:12:38,223
そして水が、水、用意してくれたんだよね？みんなに見える水。
And they prepared this water for me, right? Water that everyone can see.

142
00:12:42,023 --> 00:12:44,223
うまい！
Delicious!

143
00:12:44,223 --> 00:12:50,023
うますぎる！この、この振りはちょっと怒られそうだからもうできないけど、うますぎる！
So good! I might get scolded for doing this pose, so I won't do it again, but it's so delicious!

144
00:12:50,523 --> 00:12:52,023
うまいな。
So good.

145
00:12:52,023 --> 00:12:55,223
これで、あと1時間やるか、そういうわけにもいかないんで、
Should we just do this for another hour? No, we can't do that.

146
00:12:55,223 --> 00:12:57,823
じゃ、1回ね、お水ちょっとお返しして、
So, let me return the water first.

147
00:12:58,523 --> 00:13:04,123
それじゃあ、水分補給もさせてもらって、息も整えたんでね。
Alright, now that I'm hydrated and caught my breath,

148
00:13:04,123 --> 00:13:08,523
はい、次の曲、早速やっていきたいと思います！
let's move on to the next song right away!

149
00:13:08,523 --> 00:13:12,023
それでは、次の曲聞いてください。
Please listen to the next song.

150
00:13:12,023 --> 00:13:13,523
「白線」
'Hakusen'

151
00:13:16,823 --> 00:13:19,223
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear sky,

152
00:13:19,223 --> 00:13:24,423
あの地平を超えて
beyond that horizon.

153
00:13:24,423 --> 00:13:28,023
はい！はい！はい！はい！
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

154
00:13:28,023 --> 00:13:30,023
もっと！はい！はい！
More! Yes! Yes!

155
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:37,723
始まりはちょっと軽い期待で
It started with a little light expectation,

156
00:13:37,723 --> 00:13:40,423
そのカケラそっとポケットしまって
gently slipping those fragments into my pocket.

157
00:13:40,423 --> 00:13:45,323
屋上 遠い空の向こうを見てた
On the rooftop, I looked beyond the distant sky.

158
00:13:45,323 --> 00:13:48,223
この足でどこに行けるかなって
Wondering where these feet of mine could take me,

159
00:13:48,223 --> 00:13:51,223
わかってないけどわかってるんだ
I didn't know, yet I knew deep down.

160
00:13:51,223 --> 00:13:56,223
白昼の淡い月に手をのばした
I reached my hand out to the pale moon in broad daylight.

161
00:13:56,223 --> 00:13:58,523
かすれたエコー でも答えはもう
A faint echo, but the answer was already

162
00:13:58,523 --> 00:14:02,123
はじめからちゃんと持っていたんだよ
something I had with me from the very start.

163
00:14:02,123 --> 00:14:07,123
メイビー この想いは
Maybe this feeling...

164
00:14:07,123 --> 00:14:12,023
マスビー 熱を増して
Must be growing hotter.

165
00:14:12,023 --> 00:14:14,623
ほらね、飛べるんだ
See? I can fly.

166
00:14:14,623 --> 00:14:19,523
もっと高く 高くまで はばたいてみたい
Higher and higher, I want to spread my wings.

167
00:14:19,523 --> 00:14:22,523
今日に未来色の軌道描いて
Drawing a future-colored trajectory on today,

168
00:14:22,523 --> 00:14:25,323
地平の先まで
to the edge of the horizon.

169
00:14:25,523 --> 00:14:30,023
届かない歌はない 迷いはもうない
There is no song that cannot reach, there are no more doubts.

170
00:14:30,023 --> 00:14:33,423
どんな世界も瞬間も揺るがない
Unshaken in any world or moment,

171
00:14:33,423 --> 00:14:35,823
アイが在るから
because love is here.

172
00:14:35,823 --> 00:14:38,623
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear sky,

173
00:14:38,623 --> 00:14:41,223
不安と期待とアンビバレント
ambivalence of anxiety and anticipation.

174
00:14:41,223 --> 00:14:44,023
でも声はもう気づいてる
But my voice has already realized,

175
00:14:44,023 --> 00:14:47,323
もっと高く高く高く高く 飛んでいける
higher, higher, higher, higher, I can fly!

176
00:14:57,023 --> 00:15:00,023
途切れ途切れの
Fragmented and broken...

177
00:15:00,071 --> 00:15:02,371
紡いでたら「一途」に変わったよ
As I kept weaving, it turned into devotion.

178
00:15:02,371 --> 00:15:04,971
あたりさわりない言葉じゃ
It's not something that harmless words...

179
00:15:04,971 --> 00:15:08,071
覆いきれないほどのマイワールド
can completely cover in my world.

180
00:15:08,071 --> 00:15:10,971
明日で呼ぶ声の持ち主は
The owner of the voice that calls out tomorrow

181
00:15:10,971 --> 00:15:13,271
他でもないこの心だ
is none other than this heart.

182
00:15:13,271 --> 00:15:15,571
たった、見えていないその言葉も
Even those words that cannot be seen

183
00:15:15,571 --> 00:15:17,871
「言葉」だと足りないだけ
are simply not enough as "words".

184
00:15:17,871 --> 00:15:19,971
掴んだもの 落としたもの
Things I grasped, things I dropped...

185
00:15:19,971 --> 00:15:24,071
転んだって立って 見えた視界から
Even if I fall, I stand up, and from the view I see...

186
00:15:24,071 --> 00:15:27,071
ロックユー！解き放って
Rock you! Release it!

187
00:15:27,071 --> 00:15:29,471
ロックユー！解き放って
Rock you! Release it!

188
00:15:29,471 --> 00:15:32,371
フォーユー！響きだして
For you! Start resounding!

189
00:15:32,371 --> 00:15:34,571
フォーユー！響きだして
For you! Start resounding!

190
00:15:34,571 --> 00:15:36,771
景色変えてゆく
The scenery is changing.

191
00:15:36,771 --> 00:15:41,871
まだ遠く遠くまで 広がった空に
In the sky spread out so far, far away,

192
00:15:41,871 --> 00:15:47,471
やっと踏み出すこの一歩なんて ちっぽけだけど
this single step I finally take is tiny, but...

193
00:15:47,471 --> 00:15:52,471
届かない場所へと続いていく
it continues toward a place beyond reach.

194
00:15:52,471 --> 00:15:57,671
どんな風に雨に消えない 白線をかく
No matter the wind or rain, I'll draw a white line that won't fade.

195
00:15:57,671 --> 00:16:02,871
もっと高く高くまで 羽ばたいていたい
Higher and higher, I want to keep flapping my wings.

196
00:16:02,871 --> 00:16:08,571
そして彼方色で繋ぐ 地平で待ってて
Wait for me on the horizon, connected by distant colors.

197
00:16:08,571 --> 00:16:13,671
もう願いに嘘はない ここがスキ！
There are no more lies in my wishes. I love it here!

198
00:16:13,671 --> 00:16:19,171
どんな世界も瞬間も輝く アイがあるから
Every world and every moment shines, because there is love.

199
00:16:19,171 --> 00:16:25,571
今はただ想うこと言えばいい 「愛してるよ！！」
Now I just have to say what's on my mind: "I love you!"

200
00:16:35,071 --> 00:16:38,271
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear blue sky.

201
00:16:38,271 --> 00:16:40,971
不安と期待のアンビバレント
The ambivalence of anxiety and expectation.

202
00:16:40,971 --> 00:16:43,271
でも君はもう気づいてる
But you already know.

203
00:16:43,271 --> 00:16:48,571
もっと高く高く高く飛んでいける！
We can fly higher, higher, and higher!

204
00:17:01,071 --> 00:17:03,571
もっと
More...

205
00:17:03,571 --> 00:17:06,271
もっと
More...

206
00:17:06,271 --> 00:17:09,571
もっと
More...

207
00:17:09,571 --> 00:17:11,571
もっと
More...

208
00:17:11,571 --> 00:17:14,571
もっと
More...

209
00:17:14,571 --> 00:17:16,871
もっと
More...

210
00:17:16,871 --> 00:17:19,571
もっと
More...

211
00:17:19,571 --> 00:17:22,571
もっと
More...

212
00:17:22,571 --> 00:17:25,571
鏡よ教えて 私の証は
Mirror, mirror, tell me, where is the proof of my existence?

213
00:17:25,571 --> 00:17:28,071
どこにあるのだろう
Where could it be?

214
00:17:28,071 --> 00:17:33,571
分からない 分からないよ
I don't know, I just don't know.

215
00:17:33,571 --> 00:17:36,071
周りと比べたってさ
Comparing myself to others...

216
00:17:36,071 --> 00:17:39,071
虚しくなるだけ
only makes me feel empty.

217
00:17:39,071 --> 00:17:41,271
あのノイズが
That noise...

218
00:17:41,271 --> 00:17:44,871
涙に似た調べに 涙を奪う
steals my tears with a melody resembling them.

219
00:17:44,871 --> 00:17:47,871
切り取った風景を 道しるべにしよう
Let's make this captured scenery our signpost.

220
00:17:47,871 --> 00:17:49,871
そうだ
That's right.

221
00:17:49,871 --> 00:17:54,871
傷ついた感情も 捨てていくなら
If we are going to cast away our wounded emotions...

222
00:17:54,871 --> 00:17:57,271
そっと響くカンパネラ
The softly resounding Campanella...

223
00:17:57,271 --> 00:18:00,071
新しい未来を感じてる
makes us feel a new future.

224
00:18:00,071 --> 00:18:04,571
怖くたって進むしかないでしょ
Even if we're scared, we have to move forward, right?

225
00:18:04,571 --> 00:18:07,071
遠くまで
Far away...

226
00:18:07,071 --> 00:18:08,571
もっと もっと
more, more...

227
00:18:08,571 --> 00:18:11,271
届けこの祈りよ光となれ
reach out, this prayer, and turn into light!

228
00:18:11,271 --> 00:18:13,271
もっと もっと
More, more...

229
00:18:13,271 --> 00:18:15,571
少しずつでもいい
Even if it's just a little at a time,

230
00:18:15,571 --> 00:18:18,571
私という答えを
we will find the answer that is "me"...

231
00:18:18,571 --> 00:18:21,071
もっと
more...

232
00:18:21,071 --> 00:18:23,571
もっと
more...

233
00:18:23,571 --> 00:18:29,071
もっと もっと
more and more!

234
00:18:29,071 --> 00:18:32,071
夜空よ教えて 私の証は
Night sky, tell me, will the proof of my existence...

235
00:18:32,071 --> 00:18:34,571
輝けるのかな
be able to shine?

236
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:40,071
見つけたい 見つけたいよ
I want to find it, I really want to find it!

237
00:18:40,071 --> 00:18:42,571
誰かの決めたレールは
The rails decided by someone else

238
00:18:42,571 --> 00:18:45,571
苦しくなるだけ
just make things painful.

239
00:18:45,571 --> 00:18:51,071
ねぇ ノイズも力に変えるよ この心に誓う
Hey, I'll turn even the noise into strength. I swear it to my heart.

240
00:18:51,071 --> 00:18:55,571
錆びついた運命の 歯車を回そう
Let's turn the gears of our rusted destiny.

241
00:18:55,571 --> 00:18:57,271
ほら
See...

242
00:18:57,271 --> 00:19:01,871
飾った感情は 脱ぎ捨てるから
because I'll cast off all decorated emotions.

243
00:19:01,871 --> 00:19:04,071
そっと紡ぐシンフォニー
The softly spun symphony...

244
00:19:04,071 --> 00:19:06,871
叶えたい願いを信じてる
believes in the wishes we want to fulfill.

245
00:19:06,871 --> 00:19:11,871
胸を張って歌うしかないでしょ
We have no choice but to sing with pride, right?

246
00:19:11,871 --> 00:19:14,071
全力で
With all our might...

247
00:19:14,071 --> 00:19:17,571
もっと もっと
more, more...

248
00:19:17,571 --> 00:19:19,871
やがて希望の歌に変わる日まで
until the day it finally turns into a song of hope...

249
00:19:19,871 --> 00:19:22,071
もっと もっと
more, more...

250
00:19:22,071 --> 00:19:25,571
悩みながらでいい 全てが宝物
It's okay to worry, everything is a treasure.

251
00:19:33,071 --> 00:19:38,571
いつの日か この声を 受け取ってくれたなら
If someday you receive this voice of mine,

252
00:19:38,571 --> 00:19:44,071
この言葉を君に もう大丈夫 ひとりじゃない
then these words are for you: "It's okay now, you are not alone."

253
00:19:44,071 --> 00:19:47,571
強い想いを
These strong feelings...

254
00:19:47,571 --> 00:19:51,071
繋ぐよ 一歩踏み出してみた
I will connect. I tried taking a step forward...

255
00:19:51,071 --> 00:19:53,871
優しく世界は微笑む
and the world smiled gently.

256
00:19:53,871 --> 00:19:57,871
高鳴る気持ちに身を任せて
Leaving myself to my soaring emotions...

257
00:19:57,871 --> 00:20:00,071
さあ行こう！
let's go!

258
00:20:00,046 --> 00:20:03,046
響くカノネラ 新しい未来を感じてる
Resounding Kanonera, I feel a new future.

259
00:20:03,046 --> 00:20:07,546
コンパクトにすすむしかないでしょ
We have no choice but to move forward compactly,

260
00:20:07,546 --> 00:20:09,546
遠くまで
far away...

261
00:20:09,546 --> 00:20:15,046
もっともっと届け この祈りよ 光となって
Send this prayer further and further, becoming light.

262
00:20:15,046 --> 00:20:21,546
もっともっと 少しずつでもいい 私という答えを
More and more, even if it's little by little, the answer that is me...

263
00:20:21,546 --> 00:20:30,546
もっと もっと もっと...
More, more, more...

264
00:21:07,046 --> 00:21:14,046
雨とペトラ
[Title: Rain and Petra]

265
00:21:26,546 --> 00:21:31,546
誰かが言った いつか空は 灰になって落ちるって
Someone said that someday the sky would turn to ash and fall.

266
00:21:31,546 --> 00:21:36,046
妄想の世の中で 日々を喰らっている
Consuming my days inside a world of delusions.

267
00:21:36,046 --> 00:21:41,046
境界線を引いてしまうのも 共感覚のせいにして
Blaming synesthesia for having drawn a boundary line,

268
00:21:41,046 --> 00:21:46,046
街の灯の海で 居場所を探している
I search for a place to belong in this sea of city lights.

269
00:21:46,546 --> 00:21:51,546
どこへ行くにも この足は 退屈に染まって動かない
No matter where I go, these feet are stained with boredom and won't move.

270
00:21:56,546 --> 00:22:01,046
少しだけ先の景色が
The scenery just a little bit ahead,

271
00:22:01,046 --> 00:22:05,546
見たいだけなのに 見たいだけなのに
even though I just want to see it, even though I just want to see it.

272
00:22:05,546 --> 00:22:11,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと 頬を濡らしてしまう
If it rains, if it rains, it will surely drench my cheeks.

273
00:22:11,046 --> 00:22:15,546
枯れてしまった色ですら 愛しくなるのに
Even the colors that have withered become so lovely to me...

274
00:22:15,546 --> 00:22:20,546
目を瞑ったら 目を瞑ったらもっと 遠く霞んでしまう
If I close my eyes, if I close my eyes, it will surely blur further away.

275
00:22:20,546 --> 00:22:25,546
ふるさとなった雨の音 笑い飛ばしてくれ
Laugh away the sound of the rain that has become my home.

276
00:22:35,546 --> 00:22:40,546
誰かが言った いつか溜息は 夜に化けて歌を歌う
Someone said that someday a sigh will turn into the night and sing a song.

277
00:22:40,546 --> 00:22:45,546
妄想の世の中で 日々を喰らっている
Consuming my days inside a world of delusions.

278
00:22:45,546 --> 00:22:50,546
優しい嘘をなぞったせいで 離れる声に気付かない
Because I traced a gentle lie, I don't notice the voice growing distant.

279
00:22:55,546 --> 00:23:00,546
溶けた月が足元に落ちて
The melted moon fell at my feet,

280
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:04,546
静かに揺れていた
swaying quietly.

281
00:23:04,546 --> 00:23:09,546
夜が降ったら 夜が降ったらきっと 今日を責めてしまう
If night falls, if night falls, I'm sure I'll blame today.

282
00:23:09,546 --> 00:23:14,546
満たされない日々のそこで 夢を見ているだけ
Just dreaming at the bottom of these unfulfilled days.

283
00:23:14,546 --> 00:23:19,546
目を逸らしても 目を逸らしてもずっと 後悔と愛の隙間
Even if I look away, even if I look away, in the gap between regret and love...

284
00:23:19,546 --> 00:23:24,546
取り残されてしまう前に 手を伸ばしてくれ
Before I get left behind, reach out your hand to me.

285
00:23:34,046 --> 00:23:39,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと
If it rains, if it rains, surely...

286
00:23:39,046 --> 00:23:44,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと
If it rains, if it rains, surely...

287
00:23:44,046 --> 00:23:49,046
湿るアスファルト背に映して 俯いた
Reflecting on the damp asphalt behind me, I looked down.

288
00:23:49,046 --> 00:23:53,046
一人ぼっちで ただ明日に期待をして
All alone, just holding expectations for tomorrow.

289
00:23:53,546 --> 00:23:59,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと 頬を濡らしてしまう
If it rains, if it rains, it will surely drench my cheeks.

290
00:23:59,046 --> 00:24:03,546
枯れてしまった色ですら 愛しくなるのに
Even the colors that have withered become so lovely to me...

291
00:24:03,546 --> 00:24:08,546
目を瞑ったら 目を瞑ったらもっと 遠く霞んでしまう
If I close my eyes, if I close my eyes, it will surely blur further away.

292
00:24:08,546 --> 00:24:14,046
ふるさとなった雨の音 笑い飛ばしてくれ
Laugh away the sound of the rain that has become my home.

293
00:24:46,046 --> 00:24:50,546
繋がっていたいって 信じられる言葉
Words I can believe, saying I want to stay connected,

294
00:24:50,546 --> 00:24:55,046
だってもう昨日の僕らにおさらば
because we already said goodbye to the us of yesterday.

295
00:24:55,046 --> 00:25:00,046
青い春を過ごした 遠い稲妻
We spent our youth like a distant flash of lightning.

296
00:25:07,794 --> 00:25:10,594
繋がっていたいって 信じられる言葉
"I want to stay connected" is a word I can believe in,

297
00:25:10,594 --> 00:25:13,894
だってもう昨日の僕らにおさらば
because we've already said goodbye to the us of yesterday.

298
00:25:13,894 --> 00:25:16,894
青い春を過ごした
The blue spring we spent together...

299
00:25:16,894 --> 00:25:19,494
遠い稲妻
...and the distant lightning.

300
00:25:19,494 --> 00:25:22,094
切なく泣いて 前だけを向けたら
If only I could cry sadly and look ahead,

301
00:25:22,094 --> 00:25:25,594
きっとどんなに楽になれていたろうな
I wonder how much easier things would have been.

302
00:25:25,594 --> 00:25:29,894
この心を揺らした 一縷の望みは
This faint hope that shook my heart...

303
00:25:30,294 --> 00:25:35,594
ないものねだりは辞めた 未完成人間
...I've stopped wishing for what I can't have. An incomplete human,

304
00:25:35,594 --> 00:25:40,594
素晴らしき世界だけが
only this wonderful world...

305
00:25:40,594 --> 00:25:44,294
答えを握ってる
...holds the answer.

306
00:25:44,894 --> 00:25:47,394
諦めてしまうほど この先沢山の
Even to the point of giving up, so many...

307
00:25:47,394 --> 00:25:49,894
後悔が君を待ってるけど
...regrets are waiting for you ahead, but...

308
00:25:49,894 --> 00:25:52,594
もうない 迷いはしないよ
...no more, I won't get lost anymore!

309
00:25:52,594 --> 00:25:55,894
この傷も愛しく 思えてしまうほど
To the point where I come to love these wounds too,

310
00:25:55,894 --> 00:25:59,294
重ねてしまうよ
I'll keep overlapping them,

311
00:25:59,294 --> 00:26:02,594
不格好なまんまでいいから
because it's okay to stay imperfect!

312
00:26:02,594 --> 00:26:05,294
走れ その歩幅で
Run, at that pace!

313
00:26:05,294 --> 00:26:07,894
走れ 声轟かせてくれ
Run, let your voice roar!

314
00:26:07,894 --> 00:26:11,294
期待と不安を同じくらい抱きしめて
Embrace both expectations and anxieties equally,

315
00:26:11,294 --> 00:26:13,894
君と今を紡ぐ
spinning the present with you...

316
00:26:13,894 --> 00:26:17,594
未来照らして
...and lighting up the future.

317
00:26:29,894 --> 00:26:32,894
顔も名前も知らない僕たちが
We, who don't even know each other's faces or names,

318
00:26:32,894 --> 00:26:35,894
たった1つの音をかき鳴らす
strum a single sound.

319
00:26:36,094 --> 00:26:40,894
いたずらみたいな奇跡のような刹那
A fleeting moment, like a prank, like a miracle,

320
00:26:40,894 --> 00:26:44,294
あっという間に流れる時が
and time flows by in the blink of an eye.

321
00:26:44,294 --> 00:26:47,894
ありのままで在り続ける怖さが
The fear of continuing to remain as I am...

322
00:26:47,894 --> 00:26:52,594
失った時間は取り戻せないけれど
...we can't take back the lost time, but...

323
00:26:53,094 --> 00:26:57,094
過去を振り返ってばかりじゃ保存
If you only look back at the past...

324
00:26:57,094 --> 00:26:58,294
泣いたっていいんだ
...it's okay to cry!

325
00:26:58,294 --> 00:27:02,894
悔しさと痛みだけが
Because only frustration and pain...

326
00:27:02,894 --> 00:27:06,594
君を肯定するから
...will affirm who you are.

327
00:27:06,594 --> 00:27:10,094
大人になったら 忘れてしまうの保存
Will you forget it when you grow up?

328
00:27:10,094 --> 00:27:13,094
君との約束をした場所は
The place where we made our promise...

